EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SATURDAY TO TUESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 262300 UTC
A LARGE AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE LIES 1030 OVER THE W OF ROCKALL AT THE START
OF THE PERIOD WITH A RIDGE EXTENDING N-EWARDS OVER THE NORWEGIAN SEA.TO
THE W OF FITZROY SITS AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE CENTRE 1009. THE SYNOPTIC
SET UP REMAINS LARGELY UNCHANGED THROUGH SUNDAY AND MONDAY AS THE HIGH CONTINUES
TO BUILD TO 1034 AND PUSHES EWARDS WHILST THE RIDGE OVER THE NORWEDIAN SEA
DECLINES. THE ATLANTIC LOW CENTRE REMAINS 1009 BUT STEADILY RETREATS TOWARDS
THE S W. BY THE END OF THE PERIOD THE HIGH PRESSURE REACHES 1036 OVER THE
W OF SEA AREA HEBRIDES AND IS WELL ESTABLISHED ACROSS ALL OF THE UK AND CULLERCOATS
AREA. NEAR GALE TO GALE WINDS ARE LIKELY TO SPREAD ACROSS MUCH OF CULLERCOATS
FM THE N E TOWARDS THE END OF THE PERIOD. STRG WINDS ARE POSS ELSEWHERE THROUGHOUT
THE PERIOD BUT UNLIKELY TO REACH GALE
